<title>GERMANY: Bayer introduces SAP's R/3 group-wide.</title>
<headline>Bayer introduces SAP's R/3 group-wide.</headline>
<dateline>WALLDORF, Germany 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>German chemicals giant Bayer AG has bought the general licence to use software company SAP AG's R/3 software system group-wide, SAP said on Thursday in a statement.</p>
<p>Bayer plans to use the R/3 client-server software to run finance, personnel and logistics, as well as exploit R/3's intra- and internet capabilities, SAP added.</p>
<p>Bayer becomes the third large German chemicals group after Hoechst and BASF to buy the R/3 package, and around 600 companies in the sector worldwide now use the software.</p>
